#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:1
msgid "E0018"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `useless_loop`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:5
msgid "There is no `continue` in this loop expression, so `loop` is useless here."
msgstr "このループ式には `continue` がないため、ここでの `loop` は不要です。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:7
msgid ""
"This warning occurs when using a `loop` expression that contains no "
"`continue` statement."
msgstr "`continue` 文を含まない `loop` 式を使うと、この警告が発生します。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:11
msgid ""
"This warning is tied to the deprecated `loop` syntax. Current MoonBit "
"also reports `deprecated_syntax` for that construct, so this "
"compatibility page has no checked source example."
msgstr ""
"この警告は非推奨の `loop` 構文に紐づいています。現在の MoonBit ではこの構文に対して "
"`deprecated_syntax` も報告されるため、この互換性ページにはチェック済みのソース例はありません。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:16
msgid ""
"In legacy code, a `loop` without any `continue` statements is equivalent "
"to a block expression that will be executed only once, making the `loop` "
"keyword redundant."
msgstr ""
"レガシーコードでは、`continue` 文を含まない `loop` は一度だけ実行されるブロック式と等価であり、"
"`loop` キーワードは冗長です。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:20
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "対処"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:22
msgid ""
"Use a simpler control flow construct like `match` or `if` when the code "
"does not need to continue the loop:"
msgstr "コードがループを継続する必要がない場合は、`match` や `if` などのより単純な制御フロー構文を使ってください。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:25
msgid ""
"let count = 2\n"
"if count >= 0 {\n"
"  println(count)\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0018.md:32
msgid ""
"If the code needs to carry state across iterations, rewrite it with a "
"current `for` loop form and use `continue` only when the loop should "
"proceed to another iteration."
msgstr ""
"コードが反復間で状態を引き継ぐ必要がある場合は、現在の `for` ループ形式に書き換え、"
"ループを次の反復へ進める必要がある場合にだけ `continue` を使ってください。"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "This error occurs when using a "
#~ "`loop` expression that contains no "
#~ "`continue` statement. In MoonBit, a "
#~ "`loop` without any `continue` statements "
#~ "is equivalent to an block expression "
#~ "that will be executed only once, "
#~ "making the `loop` keyword redundant in"
#~ " such cases. You should either add"
#~ " a `continue` statement if you need"
#~ " to restart the loop from the "
#~ "beginning, or use a simpler control "
#~ "flow construct like `match` or `if`."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "Erroneous example"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let count = 2\n"
#~ "  loop count {\n"
#~ "    _..<0 => break\n"
#~ "    _ => println(count)\n"
#~ "  }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "Output:"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "2\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "Either add a `continue` statement if you need to restart the loop:"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let count = 2\n"
#~ "  loop count {\n"
#~ "    _..<0 => break\n"
#~ "    count => {\n"
#~ "      println(count)\n"
#~ "      continue count - 1\n"
#~ "    }\n"
#~ "  }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "2\n"
#~ "1\n"
#~ "0\n"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid "Or use `if`/`match` you don't need to use `continue`:"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "///|\n"
#~ "fn main {\n"
#~ "  let count = 2\n"
#~ "  match count {\n"
#~ "    _..<0 => ()\n"
#~ "    _ => println(count)\n"
#~ "  }\n"
#~ "}\n"
#~ msgstr ""
